30/01/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Representatives of the Bulgarian and Macedonian Foreign Ministries wrapped up two days of consultations Friday (27 January) in Skopje related to bilateral co-operation and Euro-Atlantic integration. The talks primarily were aimed at mapping a yearlong plan for co-operation. 
In other news, the foreign ministry in Sofia confirmed on Monday the successful resolution of a hostage drama in Nigeria. One Bulgarian and three other foreign oil workers were abducted by local militants and held hostage since 11 January. Milko Nichev, an employee of Shell, and the others were released Monday morning. (bTV, BNR, AFP, Reuters - 30/01/06; Bulgarian Government Web site - 28/01/06)
